# Project Structure

This project is a wiki application built with Next.js and PayloadCMS, which provides headless CMS functionality.

## Directory Structure

- **src/app**: Contains Next.js app router pages and layouts
  - **(home)**: Main site pages
  - **(payload)**: Admin dashboard for PayloadCMS

- **src/components**: Reusable UI components
  - [Header.tsx](mdc:src/components/Header.tsx): Site header with navigation
  - [Footer.tsx](mdc:src/components/Footer.tsx): Site footer
  - [Search.tsx](mdc:src/components/Search.tsx): Search functionality
  - [Toolbar.tsx](mdc:src/components/Toolbar.tsx): UI controls

- **src/collections**: PayloadCMS collection definitions for content types

- **src/styles**: Global styles and Tailwind CSS configuration
  - [globals.css](mdc:src/styles/globals.css): Global CSS styles

- **src/helpers**: Utility functions and helpers

## Configuration Files

- [payload.config.ts](mdc:src/payload.config.ts): PayloadCMS configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts): Tailwind CSS configuration with custom colors
- [package.json](mdc:package.json): Project dependencies and scripts

## Database

The application uses SQLite database through PayloadCMS's SQLite adapter.
